This is a mod that turns the game into map (/level) editor. A small how-to: you
load a level like you normally do, but you spawn in spectator mode (hold B to
fly up/down). Top right of the screen shows info about your coordinates and the
tile you're currently above. The bottom bar shows your current tool. Console
(your OS terminal) is useful as it logs various things, so run the game from
console and in window mode to see the logs. There are several tools to edit the
map, each is briefly documented in the source code. You change tools with keys
that normally change weapons. A tool usually does something when you press A, or
when you hold A and press arrows. There is no traditional undo, but you can make
a snapshot of the whole map with the "snapshot" tool and then restore it anytime
with "restore" tool, so keep snapshotting the map at points when it's nice. To
export (/save) the map, use the map print tool which will print the map into
console. You can then copy paste it in the source code of the game and recompile
to have the new map in the game. If the editor is confusing, study the map
format in levels.h.

